<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12134a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12134a">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12134a"> 134(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> &frac12; scripulum ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Par hasard, quand j&apos;ai baptis&eacute; tant de milliers d&apos;hommes, ai-je attendu de quelqu&apos;un d&apos;entre eux m&ecirc;me la <mark>moiti&eacute; d&apos;un <i>scripulum</i></mark>? Dites-moi et je vous le rendrai. <br><font color="green">[When I baptised so many thousand men did I perchance ever expect from any one of them as much as half a <i>scripulum</i>? Tell me and I will give it to you.]</font> <br><font color="green">[Note to scripulum:]</font> Monnaie d&apos;argent usit&eacute;e en Irlande et pesant 24 grains (14 gr.6). <br>[Silver coin then current in Ireland and weighing 24 grains (&ldquo;A grain = 0.053 gramme.&rdquo;) (14.6 gr.) Joyce, <cite>A social history of ancient Ireland</cite>, London, 1903, t. II, p.381-382. <small> Georges Dottin, <a name="GDSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#GDSP"><cite title="source">Les livres de Saint Patrick, ap&ocirc;tre de l'Irlande</cite></a> (n.d) 42/50</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
